commit.message: Don't build on 3.11 for macOS as there is no h5py build
Bump bitshuffle version number

Add the CPATH to cibw
Update README to add caveats about the binary wheels

Restrict binary wheels to x86_64 Haswell builds

This avoids the wheels accidentally being built with AVX512 instructions
and failing on many platforms. It will also increase the optimisation
level targetted on macOS platforms.
Allow setting of architecture without requiring an OpenMP build
Allow setting build architecture by environment variable

commit.message: Fix build error C2036 on Windows

Check for HDF5 headers

This allows installation from source on systems without the HDF5 headers
available.

Co-authored-by: Alexander Clausen <a.clausen@fz-juelich.de>
Allow installation without HDF5 libraries on the system

AVX512 support (#117)

Faster transposing and untransposing using AVX512 on supported systems. Up to 30% improvement over using AVX2 only. Thanks to @HackToday for contributing this!

Authored by: Wu, Kaiqiang <kaiqiang.wu@intel.com>
Co-authored-by: vesslanjin <jun.i.jin@intel.com>
